Commented on #2098 🐛 not running multiple subjects simultaneously

It looks like the underlying issue here is that C-PAC is synching the number of available cores ( --n_cpus ) to the number of available cores per participant, so it will (while this bug is present) always run one participant at a time, though it can run an analysis in multiple threads. We'll fix this in an upcoming release.
